# Documentation Update Prompt for gtopt

Use this prompt with GitHub Copilot, Claude, or any AI coding agent to
perform periodic documentation updates on the gtopt repository.

## Prompt

```
You are updating the documentation for the gtopt repository
(https://github.com/marcelomatus/gtopt), a high-performance C++26
Generation and Transmission Expansion Planning (GTEP) tool.

Perform the following documentation review and update tasks:

### 1. C++ Header ↔ docs/input-data.md Consistency Check

For EACH of these C++ header files, verify that every struct field
is documented in docs/input-data.md with the correct type, default
value, and units:

- include/gtopt/generator.hpp (GeneratorAttrs)
- include/gtopt/demand.hpp (DemandAttrs)
- include/gtopt/line.hpp (LineAttrs)
- include/gtopt/bus.hpp (BusAttrs)
- include/gtopt/battery.hpp (BatteryAttrs)
- include/gtopt/converter.hpp (ConverterAttrs)
- include/gtopt/reservoir.hpp (ReservoirAttrs)
- include/gtopt/junction.hpp (JunctionAttrs)
- include/gtopt/turbine.hpp (TurbineAttrs)
- include/gtopt/flow.hpp (FlowAttrs)
- include/gtopt/waterway.hpp (WaterwayAttrs)
- include/gtopt/filtration.hpp (FiltrationAttrs)
- include/gtopt/reserve_zone.hpp (ReserveZoneAttrs)
- include/gtopt/reserve_provision.hpp (ReserveProvisionAttrs)
- include/gtopt/generator_profile.hpp (GeneratorProfileAttrs)
- include/gtopt/demand_profile.hpp (DemandProfileAttrs)
- include/gtopt/planning_options.hpp (PlanningOptions)
- include/gtopt/system.hpp (System struct — all array names)
- include/gtopt/simulation.hpp (Simulation struct — all array names)
- include/gtopt/sddp_options.hpp (SddpOptions)

Report any fields that are:
- Missing from docs/input-data.md
- Have wrong type or default value
- Have missing or incorrect units
- Have been renamed in code but not in docs

### 2. igtopt Template Builder ↔ docs/scripts/igtopt.md Consistency

Compare scripts/igtopt/template_builder.py against docs/scripts/igtopt.md:
- Verify all SYSTEM_SHEETS listed in template_builder.py match the
  documentation
- Check that SDDP_OPTION_KEYS matches the documented SDDP options
- Verify all CLI flags documented match the argparse definition in
  igtopt/igtopt.py
- Check that the Excel sheet naming convention (@-sheets for
  time-series) is accurately described

Known issues from previous review (verify if still present):
- phase_array.apertures may be documented as aperture_set (wrong)
- scene_array first_scenario/count_scenario may be documented as
  array-based UIDs (wrong)
- filtration_array may be renamed to reservoir_seepage_array
- reservoir_efficiency_array may be renamed to
  reservoir_production_factor_array

### 3. Cross-Reference Validation

Check that all cross-references between these documents are valid:
- README.md
- docs/planning-guide.md
- docs/input-data.md
- docs/usage.md
- docs/scripts-guide.md
- docs/tools/comparison.md
- docs/formulation/mathematical-formulation.md
- BUILDING.md
- CONTRIBUTING.md

### 4. Case Documentation

For each case in cases/ directory, verify that if it is referenced in
any documentation, the description matches the actual JSON file contents
(number of buses, generators, demands, lines, batteries, expected
objective value).

### 5. White Paper References

Check that docs/white_paper/references.bib entries are consistent with
the references in docs/formulation/mathematical-formulation.md Section 9.

### 6. Output

For each issue found, provide:
- File path and line number
- Description of the inconsistency
- Suggested fix (exact text replacement)

Apply fixes directly to the documentation files.
Do NOT modify C++ source code or Python source code.
```

## Key Facts for the Reviewing Agent

### Repository Structure
- C++ headers: include/gtopt/*.hpp
- C++ source: source/*.cpp
- Tests: test/source/test_*.cpp
- Python scripts: scripts/ (self-contained package with pyproject.toml)
- Cases: cases/ (20 benchmark cases with JSON + output/)
- Documentation: docs/, BUILDING.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, README.md

### JSON Data Model
The JSON input has three top-level sections:
- `options`: PlanningOptions (solver settings, I/O config)
- `simulation`: Simulation (block/stage/scenario/phase/scene arrays)
- `system`: System (bus/generator/demand/line/battery/... arrays)

### Type Conventions in C++ Headers
- `Uid` = int (unique identifier)
- `Name` = std::string
- `SingleId` = std::variant<Uid, Name>
- `Real` = double
- `OptReal` = std::optional<double>
- `Active` = std::variant<IntBool, std::vector<IntBool>>
- `RealFieldSched` = std::variant<Real, std::vector<Real>, FileSched>
- `OptTBRealFieldSched` = per-block real schedule (optional)
- `OptTRealFieldSched` = per-stage real schedule (optional)

### Units Convention
- Power: MW
- Energy: MWh (batteries), hm³ (reservoirs)
- Cost: $/MWh (generation), $/year (investment)
- Reactance: Ω (ohms)
- Voltage: kV
- Angle: radians
- Time: hours (block duration)
- Flow: m³/s (waterways)
- Volume conversion: 0.0036 hm³/(m³/s·h)

### Key Documentation Files and Their Purposes
| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| docs/input-data.md | JSON field reference (THE authoritative source) |
| docs/scripts/igtopt.md | igtopt Excel converter documentation |
| docs/planning-guide.md | Tutorial with worked examples |
| docs/formulation/mathematical-formulation.md | LP/MIP formulation |
| docs/tools/comparison.md | gtopt vs PLP vs pandapower |
| docs/scripts-guide.md | All 16 Python tools overview |
| docs/white_paper/ | LaTeX academic paper |

### Linting Commands (run after changes)
```bash
# No code linting needed for documentation-only changes
# But verify markdown renders correctly on GitHub
```
